no response.

1:05:50.375 --> 1:05:52.291
Raise all shields.

1:05:52.333 --> 1:05:53.875
Phasers at ready.

1:05:53.917 --> 1:05:56.709
Shields up, sir,

1:05:53.917 --> 1:05:56.709
phasers ready.

1:06:12.875 --> 1:06:14.542
PICARD:

1:06:12.875 --> 1:06:14.542
Get me Groppler Zorn

1:06:14.583 --> 1:06:17.875
and continue universal

1:06:14.583 --> 1:06:17.875
greetings on all frequencies.

1:06:17.917 --> 1:06:19.667
This is Zorn, Captain.

1:06:19.709 --> 1:06:23.125
Zorn, an unidentified vessel

1:06:19.709 --> 1:06:23.125
has entered into orbit with us.

1:06:23.166 --> 1:06:25.083
Do you know who it is?

1:06:25.125 --> 1:06:27.458
There are no ships scheduled

1:06:25.125 --> 1:06:27.458
to arrive until...

1:06:27.500 --> 1:06:29.875
I asked you

1:06:27.500 --> 1:06:29.875
if you knew who it is.

1:06:29.917 --> 1:06:31.792
You mentioned the

1:06:29.917 --> 1:06:31.792
Ferengi alliance to me.

1:06:31.834 --> 1:06:36.291
But we've had

1:06:31.834 --> 1:06:36.291
no dealings with them.

1:06:36.333 --> 1:06:38.709
It was only a... a thought.

1:06:38.750 --> 1:06:40.875
Are you certain?

1:06:38.750 --> 1:06:40.875
I promise you, Captain.

1:06:40.917 --> 1:06:43.041
We were making an empty threat.

1:06:43.083 --> 1:06:46.166
I wanted your cooperation.

1:06:43.083 --> 1:06:46.166
Forgive me.

1:06:46.208 --> 1:06:48.625
Definitely entering

1:06:46.208 --> 1:06:48.625
orbital trajectory, sir.

1:06:48.667 --> 1:06:51.000
It measures 12 times

1:06:48.667 --> 1:06:51.000
our volume, Captain.

1:07:23.291 --> 1:07:26.291
The sensors say we were

1:07:23.291 --> 1:07:26.291
just scanned, sir.

1:07:31.625 --> 1:07:33.542
Pain again?

1:07:35.625 --> 1:07:38.000
Troi, you've been

1:07:35.625 --> 1:07:38.000
at it enough.

1:07:38.041 --> 1:07:39.792
No.

1:07:39.834 --> 1:07:42.250
I feel close to

1:07:39.834 --> 1:07:42.250
an answer of some kind.

1:07:42.291 --> 1:07:46.250
Commander, something down here

1:07:42.291 --> 1:07:46.250
is shielding our communicators.

1:07:46.291 --> 1:07:48.208
Yes.

1:07:48.250 --> 1:07:50.125
That's exactly the feeling

1:07:48.250 --> 1:07:50.125
I've been reading--

1:07:50.166 --> 1:07:52.917
as if someone doesn't want us

1:07:50.166 --> 1:07:52.917
to be in touch with our ship.

1:07:52.959 --> 1:07:55.542
Come on.

1:07:52.959 --> 1:07:55.542
Let's get to the surface.

1:08:02.583 --> 1:08:05.750
There is no computer record

1:08:02.583 --> 1:08:05.750
of any such vessel, sir.

1:08:05.792 --> 1:08:07.417
Nothing even close.

1:08:07.458 --> 1:08:09.041
Still no response, sir.

1:08:09.083 --> 1:08:10.917
We've done everything

1:08:09.083 --> 1:08:10.917
but threaten them.

1:08:14.166 --> 1:08:16.667
Sensor scans,

1:08:14.166 --> 1:08:16.667
Mr. Worf.

1:08:16.709 --> 1:08:19.917
Our sensor signals

1:08:16.709 --> 1:08:19.917
just seem to bounce off.

1:08:19.959 --> 1:08:21.959
Something's happening, sir.

1:08:24.417 --> 1:08:26.750
They're firing

1:08:24.417 --> 1:08:26.750
on Farpoint, sir.

1:08:26.792 --> 1:08:29.542
Bring photon torpedoes

1:08:26.792 --> 1:08:29.542
to ready.

1:08:26.792 --> 1:08:29.542
Wait, sir.

1:08:29.583 --> 1:08:31.959
They're hitting the old Bandi

1:08:29.583 --> 1:08:31.959
city, not Farpoint Station.

1:08:50.709 --> 1:08:52.917
Those stairs are where

1:08:50.709 --> 1:08:52.917
we entered down here, sir.

1:08:52.959 --> 1:08:56.250
At this point it becomes

1:08:52.959 --> 1:08:56.250
ordinary stone, sir,

1:08:52.959 --> 1:08:56.250
matching what's above.

1:08:58.458 --> 1:09:01.375
My God, was that

1:08:58.458 --> 1:09:01.375
a phaser blast?

1:09:01.417 --> 1:09:03.917
DATA:

1:09:01.417 --> 1:09:03.917
Negative, but something similar.

1:09:05.792 --> 1:09:08.709
You, Tasha, and Geordi

1:09:05.792 --> 1:09:08.709
will beam up to the ship now.

1:09:08.750 --> 1:09:11.000
Come on. I want to see

1:09:08.750 --> 1:09:11.000
exactly what's happening.

1:09:15.750 --> 1:09:18.125
Don't! If you should be hurt...

1:09:18.166 --> 1:09:20.750
You have your

1:09:18.166 --> 1:09:20.750
orders, Lieutenant.

1:09:20.792 --> 1:09:22.625
Carry them out.

1:09:22.667 --> 1:09:24.125
Yes, sir.

1:09:24.166 --> 1:09:26.291
I'm sorry, sir.

1:09:28.291 --> 1:09:31.250
<i>Enterprise,</i>

1:09:28.291 --> 1:09:31.250
three to beam up.

1:09:41.083 --> 1:09:44.333
<i>Enterprise, Enterprise,</i>

1:09:41.083 --> 1:09:44.333
come in.

1:09:44.375 --> 1:09:46.458
Help us, please.

1:09:48.792 --> 1:09:50.333
What shall we do?

1:09:50.375 --> 1:09:52.667
<i>Enterprise,</i> help us, please!

1:09:52.709 --> 1:09:54.625
Tune that down.

1:09:54.667 --> 1:09:56.792
Commander Riker, come in.

1:09:54.667 --> 1:09:56.792
Can you hear me?

1:10:02.792 --> 1:10:04.709
Riker to<i> Enterprise,</i>

1:10:02.792 --> 1:10:04.709
come in.

1:10:04.750 --> 1:10:07.291
PICARD:

1:10:04.750 --> 1:10:07.291
Commander Riker, come in.

1:10:04.750 --> 1:10:07.291
Where are you?

1:10:07.333 --> 1:10:10.291
With Data, on the edge

1:10:07.333 --> 1:10:10.291
of the old city, sir.

1:10:10.333 --> 1:10:13.375
It's being hit

1:10:10.333 --> 1:10:13.375
hard, sir.

1:10:13.417 --> 1:10:14.834
And Farpoint Station?

1:10:13.417 --> 1:10:14.834
Any damage there?

1:10:14.875 --> 1:10:17.542
Negative on damage

1:10:14.875 --> 1:10:17.542
to Farpoint, sir.

1:10:17.583 --> 1:10:19.166
Whoever they are,

1:10:19.208 --> 1:10:20.750
they're carefully avoiding

1:10:19.208 --> 1:10:20.750
hitting the Station.

1:10:20.792 --> 1:10:22.583
It's from

1:10:20.792 --> 1:10:22.583
an unidentified vessel

1:10:22.625 --> 1:10:24.208
that's entered

1:10:22.625 --> 1:10:24.208
into orbit with us here.

1:10:24.250 --> 1:10:26.709
No ID, no answer

1:10:24.250 --> 1:10:26.709
to our signals.

1:10:26.750 --> 1:10:28.959
The old Bandi city's

1:10:26.750 --> 1:10:28.959
being hit hard, sir.

1:10:29.000 --> 1:10:32.333
Many casualties

1:10:29.000 --> 1:10:32.333
very probable.

1:10:29.000 --> 1:10:32.333
Understand, Commander.

1:10:32.375 --> 1:10:34.542
Would you object to

1:10:32.375 --> 1:10:34.542
your Captain ordering

1:10:34.583 --> 1:10:36.375
a clearly illegal kidnapping?

1:10:36.417 --> 1:10:38.834
No objection, sir.

1:10:38.875 --> 1:10:41.667
Groppler Zorn may have

1:10:38.875 --> 1:10:41.667
the answers we need.

1:10:41.709 --> 1:10:43.417
Get him-- bring him here.

1:10:43.458 --> 1:10:45.375
Aye, sir.

1:10:52.375 --> 1:10:55.250
They're forcing a very difficult

1:10:52.375 --> 1:10:55.250
decision on me, Counselor.

1:10:55.291 --> 1:10:58.542
But I doubt protecting

1:10:55.291 --> 1:10:58.542
the Bandi would violate

1:10:55.291 --> 1:10:58.542
the Prime Directive.

1:10:58.583 --> 1:11:00.583
True, they are not

1:10:58.583 --> 1:11:00.583
actual allies, but...

1:11:00.625 --> 1:11:04.750
We are in the midst of

1:11:00.625 --> 1:11:04.750
diplomatic discussions

1:11:00.625 --> 1:11:04.750
with them.

1:11:04.792 --> 1:11:07.875
Lieutenant, lock

1:11:04.792 --> 1:11:07.875
phasers on that vessel.

1:11:07.917 --> 1:11:10.583
Phasers locked on,

1:11:07.917 --> 1:11:10.583
Captain.

1:11:13.000 --> 1:11:15.667
Typical, so typical.

1:11:15.709 --> 1:11:19.041
Savage life-forms never follow

1:11:15.709 --> 1:11:19.041
even their own rules.

1:11:27.083 --> 1:11:29.375
Get off my Bridge!

1:11:29.417 --> 1:11:31.458
Interesting, that

1:11:29.417 --> 1:11:31.458
order about phasers.

1:11:31.500 --> 1:11:33.208
Standing by

1:11:31.500 --> 1:11:33.208
on phasers, Captain.

1:11:33.250 --> 1:11:36.041
Please, don't let me interfere.

1:11:33.250 --> 1:11:36.041
Use your weapons.

1:11:36.083 --> 1:11:37.625
With no idea of who

1:11:36.083 --> 1:11:37.625
is on that vessel,

1:11:37.667 --> 1:11:39.542
my order was a routine

1:11:37.667 --> 1:11:39.542
safety precaution.

1:11:39.583 --> 1:11:42.250
Really? No idea of

1:11:39.583 --> 1:11:42.250
what it represents?

1:11:42.291 --> 1:11:44.208
The meaning of that

1:11:42.291 --> 1:11:44.208
vessel is as plain...

1:11:44.250 --> 1:11:47.542
as plain as the noses

1:11:44.250 --> 1:11:47.542
on your ugly little

1:11:44.250 --> 1:11:47.542
primate faces.

1:11:47.583 --> 1:11:49.583
And if you were truly

1:11:47.583 --> 1:11:49.583
civilized, Captain,

1:11:49.625 --> 1:11:51.625
wouldn't you be doing something

1:11:49.625 --> 1:11:51.625
about the casualties

1:11:51.667 --> 1:11:53.917
happening down there?

1:11:53.959 --> 1:11:56.750
Captain to CMO.

1:11:53.959 --> 1:11:56.750
Are you reading any of this?

1:11:56.792 --> 1:11:59.583
Medical teams already preparing

1:11:56.792 --> 1:11:59.583
to beam down, Captain.

1:11:59.625 --> 1:12:01.792
Compliments

1:11:59.625 --> 1:12:01.792
on that, Doctor.

1:12:01.834 --> 1:12:03.750
Any questions?

1:12:03.792 --> 1:12:06.959
Starfleet people are trained

1:12:03.792 --> 1:12:06.959
to render aid and assistance

1:12:03.792 --> 1:12:06.959
whenever...

1:12:07.000 --> 1:12:09.166
But not trained

1:12:07.000 --> 1:12:09.166
in clear thinking.

1:12:09.208 --> 1:12:11.291
Let's consider

1:12:09.208 --> 1:12:11.291
<i>your</i> thoughts.

1:12:11.333 --> 1:12:13.125
You call us savages

1:12:11.333 --> 1:12:13.125
and yet you knew

1:12:13.166 --> 1:12:15.375
those people down there

1:12:13.166 --> 1:12:15.375
were going to be killed.

1:12:15.417 --> 1:12:17.583
It is<i> your</i> conduct

1:12:15.417 --> 1:12:17.583
that is uncivilized.

1:12:17.625 --> 1:12:20.583
Sir, they're firing

1:12:17.625 --> 1:12:20.583
on the planet again.

1:12:23.417 --> 1:12:24.875
Go to maneuvering jets.

1:12:24.917 --> 1:12:27.083
Position us between

1:12:24.917 --> 1:12:27.083
that vessel and the planet.

1:12:27.125 --> 1:12:28.834
Force fields full on.

1:12:28.875 --> 1:12:31.625
Aye, sir.

1:12:31.667 --> 1:12:33.834
Impulse power to...

1:12:34.875 --> 1:12:36.792
We have no ship control, sir.

1:12:38.542 --> 1:12:39.959
It's gone.

1:12:56.375 --> 1:12:58.166
Are you undamaged?

1:12:58.208 --> 1:13:00.291
Yes. You?

1:13:08.291 --> 1:13:10.458
All systems operating.

1:13:24.750 --> 1:13:28.625
(<i> sobbing</i> )

1:13:28.667 --> 1:13:31.500
Please. Make it stop!

1:13:31.542 --> 1:13:33.625
You can drive it away.

1:13:33.667 --> 1:13:36.083
Drive who away,

1:13:33.667 --> 1:13:36.083
Groppler?

1:13:36.125 --> 1:13:38.041
I don't know.

1:13:36.125 --> 1:13:38.041
DATA:

1:13:36.125 --> 1:13:38.041
Unlikely, sir.

1:13:38.083 --> 1:13:39.750
Our records show

1:13:38.083 --> 1:13:39.750
you supervised

1:13:39.792 --> 1:13:42.291
all Bandi contact

1:13:39.792 --> 1:13:42.291
with other worlds.

1:13:42.333 --> 1:13:44.000
We've done nothing wrong.

1:13:44.041 --> 1:13:46.333
Then if we can learn

1:13:44.041 --> 1:13:46.333
nothing from you...

1:13:46.375 --> 1:13:48.041
we'll leave.

1:13:48.083 --> 1:13:49.959
No! Oh, no, please,

1:13:48.083 --> 1:13:49.959
don't leave.

1:13:50.000 --> 1:13:52.917
I'll... try to explain.

1:13:52.959 --> 1:13:55.250
(<i> screaming</i> )

1:14:01.917 --> 1:14:04.083
First Officer

1:14:01.917 --> 1:14:04.083
to<i> Enterprise.</i>

1:14:06.917 --> 1:14:09.083
We've lost Zorn.

1:14:10.792 --> 1:14:12.583
Something like

1:14:10.792 --> 1:14:12.583
a transporter beam

1:14:12.625 --> 1:14:14.166
seems to have

1:14:12.625 --> 1:14:14.166
snatched him away.

1:14:14.208 --> 1:14:18.667
Question, sir.

1:14:14.208 --> 1:14:18.667
Could it be this Q?

1:14:18.709 --> 1:14:20.750
None of you knows

1:14:18.709 --> 1:14:20.750
who transported him.

1:14:20.792 --> 1:14:22.750
You're running out

1:14:20.792 --> 1:14:22.750
of time, Captain.

1:14:22.792 --> 1:14:26.834
Captain, suddenly

1:14:22.792 --> 1:14:26.834
I'm sensing something else.

1:14:29.083 --> 1:14:32.041
Satisfaction.

1:14:32.083 --> 1:14:34.166
Enormous satisfaction.

1:14:34.208 --> 1:14:36.542
PICARD:

1:14:34.208 --> 1:14:36.542
From the same source

1:14:34.208 --> 1:14:36.542
as before?

1:14:36.583 --> 1:14:38.166
No, that was on the planet.

1:14:38.208 --> 1:14:39.166
This is much closer.

1:14:39.208 --> 1:14:40.583
Excellent, Counselor.

1:14:40.625 --> 1:14:43.208
He's such a dullard,

1:14:40.625 --> 1:14:43.208
isn't he?

1:14:45.250 --> 1:14:46.959
Captain,

1:14:45.250 --> 1:14:46.959
from Transporter Room:

1:14:47.000 --> 1:14:49.250
First Officer and Mr. Data

1:14:47.000 --> 1:14:49.250
have beamed aboard.

1:14:49.291 --> 1:14:50.792
Excellent, also.

1:14:50.834 --> 1:14:52.625
Perhaps with more of

1:14:50.834 --> 1:14:52.625
these little minds helping...

1:14:52.667 --> 1:14:54.041
That is enough, damn it!

1:14:54.083 --> 1:14:56.083
Have you forgotten that

1:14:54.083 --> 1:14:56.083
we have an agreement?

1:14:56.125 --> 1:14:57.375
An agreement which

1:14:56.125 --> 1:14:57.375
you are, at this moment,

1:14:57.417 --> 1:14:59.208
breaking by taking

1:14:57.417 --> 1:14:59.208
over our vessel

1:14:59.250 --> 1:15:01.250
interfering with my decisions.

1:15:03.166 --> 1:15:04.834
Either leave or finish us!

1:15:04.875 --> 1:15:06.458
Temper, temper,

1:15:04.875 --> 1:15:06.458
<i>mon capitaine.</i>

1:15:06.500 --> 1:15:09.667
I'm merely trying to

1:15:06.500 --> 1:15:09.667
assist a pitiful species,

1:15:09.709 --> 1:15:11.667
but perhaps I will leave...

1:15:11.709 --> 1:15:14.250
if Commander Riker provides me

1:15:11.709 --> 1:15:14.250
with some amusement.

1:15:14.291 --> 1:15:15.834
Do nothing that he asks.

1:15:15.875 --> 1:15:19.041
But I ask so little,

1:15:15.875 --> 1:15:19.041
and it's so necessary

1:15:19.083 --> 1:15:20.583
if you're to

1:15:19.083 --> 1:15:20.583
solve all this.

1:15:20.625 --> 1:15:23.041
Beam over there with

1:15:20.625 --> 1:15:23.041
your what do you call it?

1:15:23.083 --> 1:15:24.542
Your "away team"?

1:15:24.583 --> 1:15:26.667
I'll risk none of my crew

1:15:24.583 --> 1:15:26.667
on that unknown.

1:15:26.709 --> 1:15:28.875
You should already know

1:15:26.709 --> 1:15:28.875
what you'll find there,

1:15:28.917 --> 1:15:32.166
but perhaps it's too adult

1:15:28.917 --> 1:15:32.166
a puzzle for you.

1:15:32.208 --> 1:15:35.667
With all respect, Captain,

1:15:32.208 --> 1:15:35.667
I want to beam over there.

1:15:35.709 --> 1:15:38.417
You show promise,

1:15:35.709 --> 1:15:38.417
my good fellow.

1:15:38.458 --> 1:15:41.709
Have you understood any part

1:15:38.458 --> 1:15:41.709
of what he's tried to tell you?

1:15:41.750 --> 1:15:44.709
Humanity is no longer

1:15:41.750 --> 1:15:44.709
a savage race.

1:15:46.083 --> 1:15:48.709
But you must still

1:15:46.083 --> 1:15:48.709
prove that.

1:15:54.875 --> 1:15:56.959
At least you impressed him,

1:15:54.875 --> 1:15:56.959
Number One.

1:15:57.000 --> 1:15:58.041
That's hopeful.

1:15:58.083 --> 1:16:00.792
Thank you, Captain.

1:16:02.291 --> 1:16:04.250
Captain, if he's not open

1:16:02.291 --> 1:16:04.250
to evidence in our favor,

1:16:04.291 --> 1:16:06.333
where will you go

1:16:04.291 --> 1:16:06.333
from there?

1:16:06.375 --> 1:16:07.917
I'll attend to my duty.

1:16:07.959 --> 1:16:09.250
To the bitter end?

1:16:09.291 --> 1:16:12.375
I see nothing

1:16:09.291 --> 1:16:12.375
so bitter about that.

1:16:19.000 --> 1:16:21.834
Can I help you, Captain?

1:16:21.875 --> 1:16:24.709
I, uh...

1:16:24.750 --> 1:16:28.625
I didn't want you thinking me

1:16:24.750 --> 1:16:28.625
harsh, cold-blooded.

1:16:28.667 --> 1:16:30.542
Why, oh, why

1:16:28.667 --> 1:16:30.542
would I ever think that?

1:16:30.583 --> 1:16:33.625
I didn't welcome you aboard

1:16:30.583 --> 1:16:33.625
personally, professionally.

1:16:33.667 --> 1:16:35.834
I made you come to me

1:16:33.667 --> 1:16:35.834
on the Bridge.

1:16:35.875 --> 1:16:37.583
I yelled at your son,

1:16:37.625 --> 1:16:40.792
who, as you pointed out,

1:16:37.625 --> 1:16:40.792
was quite correct.

1:16:40.834 --> 1:16:42.375
He does seem to have

1:16:42.417 --> 1:16:45.041
a very good grasp of

1:16:42.417 --> 1:16:45.041
starship operations.

1:16:45.083 --> 1:16:48.625
You've just won

1:16:45.083 --> 1:16:48.625
this mother's heart, Captain.

1:16:48.667 --> 1:16:50.750
Ah.

1:16:50.792 --> 1:16:54.750
But, now,

1:16:50.792 --> 1:16:54.750
your assignment here...

1:16:54.792 --> 1:16:57.375
I would...

1:16:57.417 --> 1:17:00.166
consider and approve

1:17:00.208 --> 1:17:02.709
a transfer for you.

1:17:02.750 --> 1:17:04.458
Oh.

1:17:04.500 --> 1:17:07.834
Do you consider me

1:17:04.500 --> 1:17:07.834
unqualified?

1:17:04.500 --> 1:17:07.834
Hardly.

1:17:07.875 --> 1:17:11.000
Your service record shows

1:17:07.875 --> 1:17:11.000
you're just the chief

1:17:07.875 --> 1:17:11.000
medical officer I want.

1:17:11.041 --> 1:17:12.959
Then you must object to me

1:17:11.041 --> 1:17:12.959
personally.

1:17:13.000 --> 1:17:15.667
I'm trying to be considerate

1:17:13.000 --> 1:17:15.667
of your feelings, Doctor.

1:17:15.709 --> 1:17:18.583
For you to work

1:17:15.709 --> 1:17:18.583
with a commanding officer

1:17:18.625 --> 1:17:20.834
who would

1:17:18.625 --> 1:17:20.834
continually remind you

1:17:20.875 --> 1:17:23.291
of a terrible,

1:17:20.875 --> 1:17:23.291
personal tragedy...

1:17:23.333 --> 1:17:25.542
If I had had any objections

1:17:23.333 --> 1:17:25.542
to serving with you,

1:17:25.583 --> 1:17:28.291
I wouldn't have requested

1:17:25.583 --> 1:17:28.291
this assignment, Captain.

1:17:28.333 --> 1:17:31.542
You requested this posting?

1:17:31.583 --> 1:17:34.250
My feelings about my husband's

1:17:31.583 --> 1:17:34.250
death will have no effect

1:17:34.291 --> 1:17:37.208
on the way I serve you,

1:17:34.291 --> 1:17:37.208
this vessel, or this mission.

1:17:39.291 --> 1:17:41.625
Ah.

1:17:41.667 --> 1:17:44.333
Then welcome aboard,

1:17:41.667 --> 1:17:44.333
Doctor.

1:17:44.375 --> 1:17:46.291
<i>Riker to Picard.</i>

1:17:46.333 --> 1:17:49.583
<i>We're ready to beam over, sir.</i>

1:17:49.625 --> 1:17:52.959
I, uh...I hope

1:17:49.625 --> 1:17:52.959
we can be friends.

1:17:53.000 --> 1:17:55.291
Thank you.

1:18:06.792 --> 1:18:08.583
Phasers on stun.

1:18:14.625 --> 1:18:16.166
Energize.

1:18:35.583 --> 1:18:37.500
Most interesting, sir.

1:18:39.417 --> 1:18:41.417
Much the same

1:18:39.417 --> 1:18:41.417
construction we saw

1:18:41.458 --> 1:18:43.000
in the underground tunnel.

1:18:43.041 --> 1:18:45.458
But no sound of power.

1:18:45.500 --> 1:18:47.500
No equipment.

1:18:47.542 --> 1:18:50.041
How does this ship run?

1:18:51.750 --> 1:18:54.542
(<i> gasp of pain</i> )

1:18:51.750 --> 1:18:54.542
What is it, Troi?

1:18:54.583 --> 1:18:56.917
Is it the same

1:18:54.583 --> 1:18:56.917
as you felt down there?

1:18:56.959 --> 1:18:58.709
No.

1:18:58.750 --> 1:19:01.917
This is much

1:18:58.750 --> 1:19:01.917
more powerful.

1:19:01.959 --> 1:19:05.583
Full of anger.

1:19:05.625 --> 1:19:07.542
Hate.

1:19:07.583 --> 1:19:08.959
Toward us?

1:19:09.000 --> 1:19:10.834
No.

1:19:10.875 --> 1:19:14.542
It's directed down

1:19:10.875 --> 1:19:14.542
toward the old Bandi city.

1:19:14.583 --> 1:19:16.667
Most intriguing

1:19:14.583 --> 1:19:16.667
again, sir.

1:19:16.709 --> 1:19:19.917
The place that

1:19:16.709 --> 1:19:19.917
this vessel was

1:19:16.709 --> 1:19:19.917
firing upon

1:19:19.959 --> 1:19:21.709
was not the

1:19:19.959 --> 1:19:21.709
Farpoint Starbase

1:19:21.750 --> 1:19:24.959
but the home of those

1:19:21.750 --> 1:19:24.959
who constructed...

1:19:26.750 --> 1:19:29.709
Sorry, sir.

1:19:29.750 --> 1:19:33.583
I seem to be

1:19:29.750 --> 1:19:33.583
commenting on everything.

1:19:33.625 --> 1:19:35.792
Good.

1:19:35.834 --> 1:19:37.667
Don't stop, my friend.

1:19:43.667 --> 1:19:46.000
<i>Enterprise,</i> Riker.

1:19:46.041 --> 1:19:50.166
This is turning out to be a very

1:19:46.041 --> 1:19:50.166
long tunnel or corridor, sir.

1:19:50.208 --> 1:19:52.000
No ship's crew in sight.

1:19:52.041 --> 1:19:54.875
No sign of mechanism

1:19:52.041 --> 1:19:54.875
or circuitry.

1:19:54.917 --> 1:19:57.750
No controls or readouts.

1:19:59.166 --> 1:20:02.458
This is nothing like

1:19:59.166 --> 1:20:02.458
any vessel I've seen before.

1:20:02.500 --> 1:20:04.792
Groppler Zorn, sir...

1:20:04.834 --> 1:20:07.959
in great fear, just ahead.

1:20:08.000 --> 1:20:11.834
There is a different feeling

1:20:08.000 --> 1:20:11.834
here than in the tunnel.

1:20:11.875 --> 1:20:14.250
Very different.

1:20:14.291 --> 1:20:18.959
ZORN (<i> in distance</i> ):

1:20:14.291 --> 1:20:18.959
No, please! No more, please!

1:20:19.000 --> 1:20:21.083
No more!

1:20:22.500 --> 1:20:26.625
Please, make it stop the pain!

1:20:26.667 --> 1:20:31.625
Please...

1:20:26.667 --> 1:20:31.625
make it stop the pain!

1:20:34.083 --> 1:20:36.208
No, please! No more!

1:20:36.250 --> 1:20:39.625
Please! No more!

1:20:39.667 --> 1:20:41.166
Please!

1:20:41.208 --> 1:20:42.959
Zorn, can you hear me?

1:20:43.000 --> 1:20:44.709
Make it stop the pain!

1:20:44.750 --> 1:20:47.750
(<i> screaming</i> )

1:20:47.792 --> 1:20:50.125
Has the alien communicated?

1:20:50.166 --> 1:20:52.041
Please!

1:20:52.083 --> 1:20:54.834
That's it, sir.

1:20:54.875 --> 1:20:58.000
It's just one alien

1:20:54.875 --> 1:20:58.000
I'm sensing here.

1:20:58.041 --> 1:21:01.667
Please, I don't understand

1:20:58.041 --> 1:21:01.667
what you want!

1:21:01.709 --> 1:21:03.125
Not true.

1:21:01.709 --> 1:21:03.125
He does know.

1:21:03.166 --> 1:21:06.041
ZORN:

1:21:03.166 --> 1:21:06.041
No, please! No more!

1:21:03.166 --> 1:21:06.041
Please! No more!

1:21:06.083 --> 1:21:09.500
(<i> crying</i> )

1:21:09.542 --> 1:21:12.959
No! Don't! Don't!

1:21:21.625 --> 1:21:23.208
Captain!

1:21:23.250 --> 1:21:26.500
PICARD:

1:21:23.250 --> 1:21:26.500
Transporter Chief,

1:21:23.250 --> 1:21:26.500
yank them back-- now!

1:21:27.500 --> 1:21:30.291
Riker, acknowledge.

1:21:30.333 --> 1:21:32.375
Your time is up, Captain.

1:21:32.417 --> 1:21:36.000
Transporter Chief,

1:21:32.417 --> 1:21:36.000
do you have their coordinates?

1:21:36.041 --> 1:21:38.250
Transporter Chief!

1:21:36.041 --> 1:21:38.250
He can't hear you, Captain.

1:21:38.291 --> 1:21:40.375
Transporter Chief, come in!

1:21:45.750 --> 1:21:49.625
I've people in trouble

1:21:45.750 --> 1:21:49.625
over there, Q.

1:21:55.500 --> 1:21:57.834
Everyone at ease.

1:21:55.500 --> 1:21:57.834
That's an order.

1:22:00.291 --> 1:22:04.291
Q, my people are in trouble.

1:22:04.333 --> 1:22:06.500
Let me help them, please.

1:22:11.208 --> 1:22:13.333
I'll do whatever you say.

1:22:20.250 --> 1:22:22.458
You'll do whatever I say?

1:22:25.291 --> 1:22:27.542
Seems I did make

1:22:25.291 --> 1:22:27.542
that bargain.

1:22:27.583 --> 1:22:29.208
The agreement

1:22:27.583 --> 1:22:29.208
isn't valid, sir.

1:22:29.250 --> 1:22:30.917
It wasn't Q that saved us.

1:22:30.959 --> 1:22:33.000
Save yourself.

1:22:30.959 --> 1:22:33.000
It may attack you now.

1:22:33.041 --> 1:22:35.875
It was<i> that</i> which

1:22:33.041 --> 1:22:35.875
sent us back, Captain.

1:22:35.917 --> 1:22:39.375
Yes, sir. It is not merely

1:22:35.917 --> 1:22:39.375
a vessel-- somehow it is alive.

1:22:39.417 --> 1:22:41.667
She lies! Destroy it

1:22:39.417 --> 1:22:41.667
while you have a chance.

1:22:41.709 --> 1:22:43.834
Make phasers and

1:22:41.709 --> 1:22:43.834
photon torpedoes ready.

1:22:43.875 --> 1:22:45.291
No, do nothing

1:22:43.875 --> 1:22:45.291
he demands.

1:22:45.333 --> 1:22:47.333
Captain, that thing

1:22:45.333 --> 1:22:47.333
was killing my people.

1:22:47.375 --> 1:22:49.792
Was there a reason?

1:22:47.375 --> 1:22:49.792
It is an unknown, Captain.

1:22:49.834 --> 1:22:51.417
Isn't that enough?

1:22:51.458 --> 1:22:53.625
If you'd earned that

1:22:51.458 --> 1:22:53.625
uniform you're wearing,

1:22:53.667 --> 1:22:56.417
you'd know that the unknown

1:22:53.667 --> 1:22:56.417
is what brings us out here.

1:22:56.458 --> 1:22:58.917
Wasted effort,

1:22:56.458 --> 1:22:58.917
considering human intelligence.

1:22:58.959 --> 1:23:00.625
Let's test that!

1:23:00.667 --> 1:23:03.125
Beginning with the tunnels you

1:23:00.667 --> 1:23:03.125
have under Farpoint, Groppler.

1:23:03.166 --> 1:23:06.583
Identical to those on the space

1:23:03.166 --> 1:23:06.583
vessel life-form over there.

1:23:06.625 --> 1:23:08.667
Why was it punishing you,

1:23:06.625 --> 1:23:08.667
Groppler?

1:23:08.709 --> 1:23:12.125
In return for some pain

1:23:08.709 --> 1:23:12.125
you've given another creature?

1:23:12.166 --> 1:23:13.834
We've done nothing wrong!

1:23:13.875 --> 1:23:15.709
It was injured.

1:23:13.875 --> 1:23:15.709
We helped it.

1:23:17.291 --> 1:23:20.208
Thank you.

1:23:20.250 --> 1:23:22.750
That was the

1:23:20.250 --> 1:23:22.750
missing element.

1:23:22.792 --> 1:23:27.542
Lieutenant Yar, rig main phaser

1:23:22.792 --> 1:23:27.542
banks to deliver an energy beam.

1:23:27.583 --> 1:23:28.750
Aye, sir.

1:23:28.792 --> 1:23:30.417
You're right, Captain.

1:23:30.458 --> 1:23:33.250
It has to be conceivable

1:23:30.458 --> 1:23:33.250
that somewhere in this galaxy

1:23:33.291 --> 1:23:36.750
there could exist creatures able

1:23:33.291 --> 1:23:36.750
to convert energy into matter.

1:23:36.792 --> 1:23:39.875
And into specific

1:23:36.792 --> 1:23:39.875
patterns of matter

1:23:39.917 --> 1:23:41.542
just as our transporters do.

1:23:41.583 --> 1:23:43.959
On the viewer, Captain.

1:24:18.291 --> 1:24:20.083
Groppler...

1:24:20.125 --> 1:24:24.709
you captured something

1:24:20.125 --> 1:24:24.709
like that, didn't you?

1:24:26.458 --> 1:24:30.000
Warn my people, please, to leave

1:24:26.458 --> 1:24:30.000
Farpoint Station immediately!

1:24:30.041 --> 1:24:31.417
He lies, Captain.

1:24:31.458 --> 1:24:33.000
Shouldn't you let

1:24:31.458 --> 1:24:33.000
his people die?

1:24:33.041 --> 1:24:34.333
Transmit the message:

1:24:34.375 --> 1:24:36.041
"Leave Farpoint Space

1:24:34.375 --> 1:24:36.041
Station immediately."

1:24:36.083 --> 1:24:38.375
TROI:

1:24:36.083 --> 1:24:38.375
Then it was a pair

1:24:36.083 --> 1:24:38.375
of creatures I was sensing--

1:24:38.417 --> 1:24:41.750
one down there

1:24:38.417 --> 1:24:41.750
in grief and pain,

1:24:41.792 --> 1:24:44.875
the other up here,

1:24:41.792 --> 1:24:44.875
filled with anger.

1:24:44.917 --> 1:24:47.208
DATA:

1:24:44.917 --> 1:24:47.208
And firing not on

1:24:44.917 --> 1:24:47.208
the new space station,

1:24:47.250 --> 1:24:50.542
but on the Bandi

1:24:47.250 --> 1:24:50.542
and their city.

1:24:50.583 --> 1:24:54.750
Attacking those

1:24:50.583 --> 1:24:54.750
who had captured...

1:24:56.291 --> 1:24:58.709
captured its mate.

1:25:05.041 --> 1:25:07.000
Energy beam ready, sir.

1:25:08.041 --> 1:25:09.959
Lock it in on

1:25:08.041 --> 1:25:09.959
Farpoint Station.

1:25:11.709 --> 1:25:15.208
I see now it was

1:25:11.709 --> 1:25:15.208
too simple a puzzle.

1:25:15.250 --> 1:25:19.000
Generosity has always

1:25:15.250 --> 1:25:19.000
been my... weakness.

1:25:19.041 --> 1:25:22.458
Let it have whatever

1:25:19.041 --> 1:25:22.458
it can absorb.

1:25:22.500 --> 1:25:25.125
Energize.

1:25:42.542 --> 1:25:45.041
Now getting feedback

1:25:42.542 --> 1:25:45.041
on the beam, sir.

1:25:45.083 --> 1:25:47.458
Discontinue it.

1:25:47.500 --> 1:25:49.500
Groppler Zorn...

1:25:49.542 --> 1:25:52.417
there will soon be

1:25:49.542 --> 1:25:52.417
no Farpoint Station

1:25:52.458 --> 1:25:53.959
if I'm right about this.

1:25:54.000 --> 1:25:56.000
Lucky guess!

1:26:14.667 --> 1:26:17.333
Please believe me,

1:26:17.375 --> 1:26:19.291
we meant no harm

1:26:17.375 --> 1:26:19.291
to the creature.

1:26:19.333 --> 1:26:20.792
It was starving for energy.

1:26:20.834 --> 1:26:23.000
Which your world furnishes

1:26:20.834 --> 1:26:23.000
you in plenty.

1:26:23.041 --> 1:26:24.500
And we did feed it.

1:26:24.542 --> 1:26:26.667
But only enough

1:26:24.542 --> 1:26:26.667
to keep it alive

1:26:26.709 --> 1:26:28.417
so that you could force

1:26:26.709 --> 1:26:28.417
it to shape itself

1:26:28.458 --> 1:26:30.583
into whatever

1:26:28.458 --> 1:26:30.583
form you needed.

1:27:45.250 --> 1:27:47.792
Sir...

1:27:47.834 --> 1:27:50.709
it's wonderful!

1:27:54.250 --> 1:27:57.458
A feeling of great joy...

1:27:59.250 --> 1:28:01.917
and gratitude.

1:28:05.500 --> 1:28:07.542
Great joy...

1:28:07.583 --> 1:28:10.250
and gratitude...

1:28:12.583 --> 1:28:15.542
from both of them.

1:28:33.625 --> 1:28:36.000
Why...

1:28:36.041 --> 1:28:39.583
do you use other life-forms

1:28:36.041 --> 1:28:39.583
for your recreation?

1:28:39.625 --> 1:28:41.834
If so, you've not

1:28:39.625 --> 1:28:41.834
provided the best...

1:28:41.875 --> 1:28:44.875
Leave us! We've passed

1:28:41.875 --> 1:28:44.875
your little test.

1:28:44.917 --> 1:28:47.333
Temper, temper,

1:28:44.917 --> 1:28:47.333
<i>mon capitaine.</i>

1:28:47.375 --> 1:28:49.000
Get off my ship.

1:28:49.041 --> 1:28:52.083
I do so only because

1:28:49.041 --> 1:28:52.083
it suits me to leave.

1:28:55.250 --> 1:28:58.583
But I will not promise

1:28:55.250 --> 1:28:58.583
never to appear again.

1:29:11.667 --> 1:29:15.750
<i>Captain's Log,</i>

1:29:11.667 --> 1:29:15.750
<i>Stardate 41174.2:</i>

1:29:15.792 --> 1:29:17.625
<i>The agreement</i>

1:29:15.792 --> 1:29:17.625
<i>for the rebuilding</i>

1:29:17.667 --> 1:29:20.083
<i>of Farpoint Station</i>

1:29:17.667 --> 1:29:20.083
<i>has been completed</i>

1:29:20.125 --> 1:29:21.750
<i>per my instructions.</i>

1:29:21.792 --> 1:29:23.041
All stations?

1:29:23.083 --> 1:29:25.041
Ready for departure, sir.

1:29:27.667 --> 1:29:29.291
Some problem, Riker?

1:29:29.333 --> 1:29:31.250
Just hoping this isn't

1:29:29.333 --> 1:29:31.250
the usual way

1:29:31.291 --> 1:29:32.792
our missions

1:29:31.291 --> 1:29:32.792
will go, sir.

1:29:32.834 --> 1:29:34.333
Oh, no, Number One.

1:29:34.375 --> 1:29:37.375
I'm sure most will be

1:29:34.375 --> 1:29:37.375
much more interesting.

1:29:40.333 --> 1:29:42.500
Let's see what's out there.

1:29:44.291 --> 1:29:45.375
Engage.
